from pathlib import Path
newp = Path('django/django/db/models/sql/query.py')
new = newp.read_text()
# create a fake original by replacing our function with the old assert form
old_func = '''    def change_aliases(self, change_map):
        """
        Change the aliases in change_map (which maps old-alias -> new-alias),
        relabelling any references to them in select columns and the where
        clause.
        """
        assert set(change_map).isdisjoint(change_map.values())
'''
# find existing function
start = new.find('\n    def change_aliases(')
end = new.find('\n    def bump_prefix(', start)
orig = new[:start] + '\n' + old_func + new[end:]
from difflib import unified_diff
ud = unified_diff(orig.splitlines(keepends=True), new.splitlines(keepends=True), fromfile='a/query.py', tofile='b/query.py')
open('/workspace/diff.txt','w').writelines(ud)
print('wrote /workspace/diff.txt')
